 Rituparna: Dance all the way. Picture by Pabitra Das 

 Shyama

 Rituparna Sengupta plays the charming courtesan Shyama, torn between Bajrasen and Uttiya, in this opulent adaptation of Rabindranath Tagore?s dance drama. Performed with her troupe Bhavna Aaj O Kaal, comprising dancers from Bangladesh, the piece has been choreographed by Rituparna herself. Swagatalakshmi Dasgupta, Indranil Sen and Srikanta Acharya have rendered the soulful Tagore songs, while percussionist Bikram Ghosh has composed the background score.

 Catch it on ETV Bangla, 9.30 pm, May 7

 Raktakarabi

 When the invisible ruler of Jakshapuri assumes immense control over his subjects, Nandini arrives as a whiff of fresh air, trying to break the shackles of slavery. She loves Ranjan, the dynamic youth who sacrifices his life for the good of Jakshapuri. The six-episode adaptation of Tagore?s popular drama Raktakarabi, directed by Manish Ghosh, features Gargi Roy Chowdhury, Kaushik Sen and Debesh Roy Chowdhury. 

 Catch it on Akash, 7.05 pm, May 9 to 14




